node.text:
Well hello again Monday! I hope everyone had a great weekend! One of the greatest moments is realizing that a few weeks ago your body couldn’t do what it just did. Celebrate your progress no matter how large or small it may be! Strive for progress, not perfection. You are capable of anything and everything you want to achieve. So here is your Monday reminder of how amazing and powerful YOU are! It’s a new day, new week, new goals! 

LIKE and SAVE this vid for your next sesh 💪🏼

node.text: Happy 🍑 day fam! I hope everyone is having a good week! I decided to film my work out from Monday ( I usually film IG workout vids separately on a content day but I think I like this style better ) I did a full body blast with ankle weights and dumbbells and whoosh I’m still sore 💦 Let me know in the comments below if you prefer these longer workout videos as I’m here to motivate y’all!! REMEMBER, you will never regret a workout. SAVE this vid for your next sesh 💪🏼

node.text:
🏈 Game day🍎 You know I’m all about those quick and easy @idreamaboutfood healthy snacks that satisfy your sweet tooth! Let’s talk about these APPLE NACHOS!! For starters, you can completely customize these with whatever topics you want. Chocolate and PB is a must though!!   

The topping options are endless, but I LOVE the below 
•PB, chocolate chips, cacao spread, granola. 

🍎If you make them, be sure to tag me and @idreamaboutfood so I can see and repost!  I love seeing how creative and inspired you get with the recipes I share😍

node.text: Who wants to join my next sunset workout?!  Something I’m always asked is how do I stay motivated all the time. I know my posts come off that way but sometimes I just don’t have it in me! We all have days where we just can’t get up and perform like we want to. And guess what? It’s ok! Taking some personal time and re-charging your battery is the most important and essential. Tomorrow is always a new day to start fresh and bounce back! 💪🏼💕

node.text:
As many gyms are still closed or for those who never had a gym membership, I repeat you don’t need a gym to get fit! From my own personal experience – I can tell you, it can be done!   What do you need to start? That is the best part –you really don’t need anything but yourself and a mental commitment.
﻿
﻿
﻿1. Establish a routine. Figure out what time works best for you. Morning? Evening? Once you establish a time, commit to work out at that time.
﻿
﻿2. Find a space.
﻿a) Get outdoors! Go for a jog or walk outside! It is a simple way to burn calories and improve your endurance.
﻿
﻿b) Anywhere – living room, bedroom, hotel room, office or garage. You can do simple work outs in any space just double your body size!
﻿
﻿3. Follow a workout program to keep you accountable
﻿
﻿4. Add strength. If bodyweight is not challenging enough you can add strength into your workouts without investing in equipment. Use what is around you such as canned food, textbooks, or gallons of milk/water. All can be used as hand weights to increase the level of work you do.
﻿
﻿5. Find a workout buddy online ( my private Facebook group is the perfect place for this, dm me to join )  It will help keep you motivated and more committed. You can use a fitness app too! There are several options that can help keep track of your fitness level and your calorie intake! (  I personally don’t track my calories or that would drive me crazy, you know I am all about listening to your body)
﻿
﻿You have what it takes – it is all about a positive mindset and making it happen. Make the commitment and you will begin to feel better inside and out :) I am also always here if you need someone to talk to or an extra push of motivation!!
﻿
﻿

node.text: How is everyone’s weekend going?! Never underestimate the power of your own body! Let your body be the machine that will help push you through these uncertain times. Link in my bio for my workout programs if you do want help keeping yourself accountable 💪🏼

node.text:
Raise your hand if you've made banana bread at least once during quarantine!! If you're looking to switch things up, try this bad boy!! Be sure to tag me in your posts so I can see your @blendjet  creations! #chefJ

INGREDIENTS 
2 cups flour
1 teaspoon baking soda 
3/4 teaspoon baking powder
3/4 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon cinnamon

1/2 cup pumpkin puree
1.2 cup pure maple syrup or honey
2 tablespoons of sweetener
1/3 cup oil or milk of choice
2 teaspoons pure vanilla extract
1.2 cup mini chocolate chips 
DIRECTIONS: 
STEP 1️⃣: Preheat your oven to 375ºF
STEP 2️⃣: Grease your pan
STEP 3️⃣: Add all dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl bowl. ***Add your wet ingredients into another bowl. Makes things easier on yourself in the kitchen by blending your almond milk and bananas in your @blendjet portable blender! 
STEP 4️⃣: Add your wet ingredients to your into dry ingredients and mix until smooth! 
STEP 5️⃣Bake 20 minutes AND ENOY!

node.text:
RISE AND SHINE, workout time in my @guess  👏🏻

 I’ve been getting a lot of messages from you guys about lacking motivation to workout!!  I just wanted to remind you that you’re not alone and I know it is hard to break through that slump but you got this. Everyday is a new day to start fresh. 

So, don’t beat yourself up about your appearance, your current fitness level, or your lack of motivation because you will just continue to demotivate yourself! Instead tell yourself “ I CAN ” and start today! Go get some movement in, even if it’s just a nice little walk!! The only bad workout is the one you didn’t do. 

 #GuessActive

node.text: If you want to start seeing success in your life, you need to start celebrating the small wins. Things that happen on a daily basis that push you closer to your goals!  This mindset is going to start conditioning your mind to accept more success in your life.. So tell me, what was 1 small win that happened this week?!
